                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d851">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/762: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at San José</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chase</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-14T16:00:00-05:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 14, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received July 16, 12.40 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consular Agent Saxe reports increasing aggravated conditions in Puntarenas,
                    including forcible search by soldiers of one American home and an American
                    seaman robbed of $40 by Tinoco soldiers. <pb facs="0947" n="845" xml:id="pg_845"
                    /> Also continued fighting on the Nicaraguan frontier. He suggests, and I
                    strongly recommend sending naval vessel Puntarenas, at least for time. <hi
                        rend="italic">Castine</hi> must go to Colon for repairs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chase</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
